<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=268&amp;p=3775#p3775"><![CDATA[
And here we have another! I wonder how many people have been waiting for this one:<br /><br />Pocket Bomberman!<br /><br /><a href="http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/pocketbm.zip" class="postlink">http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/pocketbm.zip</a><br /><br />What I do is I use No$Gmb to find the proper banks and addresses that I need, then I use a hex editor to extract the banks I need, then I add a bootstrap before $4000, then it usually works, but when it doesn't, I look over the code in the rom, and then see if I need to modify something. I don't actually debug the gbs itself. Mostly because I don't have anything to turn it into a rom.<br /><br />That usually is enough to get a working gbs, but I kinda break the rule of "clean it up!". <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /><br /><br />Edit (because I don't like replying to my own posts):<br />Now, Krusty's Fun House<br /><br /><a href="http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/krusty.zip" class="postlink">http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/krusty.zip</a><br /><br />Yeah, I know this has an NSF counterpart which sounds almost the same, but there are still some differences, and besides, the world needs more GBS files!<br /><br />edit 2:<br />World Bowling<br /><br /><a href="http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/wbowling.zip" class="postlink">http://drag.wootest.net/music/gbs/wbowling.zip</a><br /><br />Not a whole lot of songs though... then again, it's a bowling game.<br /><br />edit 3:<br />Been a while, just want to say that you can now find all of my gbs rips (including new ones I rip) at:<br /><br /><a href="http://drag.wootest.net/gbs/" class="postlink">http://drag.wootest.net/gbs/</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21">Drag</a> — Mon Aug 15, 2005 8:58 pm</p><hr />
